[The report says that of the 47 cholera infections alleged to have occurred in Old Havana (Havana Viejo), 33 were in individuals from the 5 eastern provinces that have been reported to continue to have cases but 17 cases have been reported to have been acquired in the Cuban capital. 33 plus 17 make 50, so the numbers do not add up. Clarification would be appreciated. - Mod.LL

